<Layout title="About Us | 20+ Years Experience | Long Beach, CA">
    <Container>
        <div class="max-w-6xl px-4 pt-16 pb-12 mx-auto">
            
            <!-- Header -->
            <div class="text-center mb-12">
                <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100 mb-4">About Us</h1>
                <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Senior engineers who ship products fast. Direct access, no bureaucracy.</p>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Who We Are -->
            <div class="bg-slate-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-2xl p-6 mb-12 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100 mb-6 text-center">Team & Approach</h2>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-neutral-900 p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100 mb-3">Our Team</h3>
                        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                            <li>• <strong>5-person engineering team</strong> expandable to 8 engineers on short notice</li>
                            <li>• <strong>20+ years combined experience</strong> building and shipping electronics, with deep biomedical expertise</li>
                            <li>• <strong>Former engineering roles</strong> at automotive, biomedical, and consumer electronics companies</li>
                            <li>• <strong>Long Beach based</strong>, serving clients nationwide via remote collaboration</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-neutral-900 p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100 mb-3">Scaling Approach</h3>
                        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                            <li>• <strong>Right-sized for focused projects</strong> - optimal team attention</li>
                            <li>• <strong>Partner network</strong> for larger projects requiring scale</li>
                            <li>• <strong>Clean handoffs</strong> to established firms when needed</li>
                            <li>• <strong>Best of both worlds</strong> - startup agility with enterprise backing</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-neutral-900 p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100 mb-3">Industries We Work With</h3>
                        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                            <li>• Biomedical devices</li>
                            <li>• Industrial automation & robotics</li>
                            <li>• Consumer electronics</li>
                            <li>• Scientific instrumentation</li>
                            <li>• Open to any industry with interesting challenges</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Our Approach vs Established Firms -->
            <div class="bg-slate-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-2xl p-6 mb-12 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100 text-center mb-6">Our Approach vs Established Firms</h2>
                
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
                    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-neutral-900 p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100 mb-3">Established Firms</h3>
                        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                            <li>• <strong>Comfortable with their reputation</strong> - they know they'll get new clients regardless</li>
                            <li>• <strong>Assign junior staff to reduce costs</strong> - seniors are "too expensive" for most projects</li>
                            <li>• <strong>Process-heavy and slow</strong> - bureaucracy protects them from accountability</li>
                            <li>• <strong>Lost the passion</strong> - engineering becomes routine, not exciting</li>
                            <li>• <strong>Take clients for granted</strong> - you're just another invoice</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-neutral-900 p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100 mb-3">Our Approach</h3>
                        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                            <li>• <strong>Senior engineers on every project</strong> - no junior staff</li>
                            <li>• <strong>Fast and direct</strong> - talk directly to the engineers</li>
                            <li>• <strong>We actually like this stuff</strong> - engineering is what we do for fun</li>
                            <li>• <strong>Your project is our reputation</strong> - we need you to win</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="text-center mt-6 p-4 bg-white dark:bg-neutral-900 rounded-xl max-w-2xl mx-auto border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 font-medium">
                        <strong>Bottom line:</strong> Senior-level engineering at accessible rates with direct access.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Recent Projects -->
            <div class="bg-slate-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-2xl p-6 mb-12 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100 text-center mb-6">Recent Projects</h2>
                
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <!-- Medical Project -->
                    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-orange-100 dark:from-orange-900/20 dark:to-orange-800/10 p-6 rounded-xl border border-orange-200 dark:border-orange-800/50">
                        <div class="mb-3">
                            <span class="text-xs font-bold text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400 uppercase tracking-wide">Medical Device • $35K • 6 months</span>
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100 mb-3">Ultrasound Motor Control System</h3>
                        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
                            <div>
                                <p class="font-medium text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200 mb-1">Challenge:</p>
                                <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">Client's ultrasound equipment needed 0.1mm positioning resolution for new market release. Existing motion control system was failing EMC tests due to spurious emissions. Manufacturing costs were too high and assembly was complex. System had to work with existing ultrasound architecture without redesigning the mechanical components.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <p class="font-medium text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200 mb-1">Technical Approach:</p>
                                <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">Designed compact 6-layer PCB with proper signal routing and EMI reduction using Pi filters, strategic component placement, and other filtering techniques. Implemented motor control algorithms with high-resolution encoder feedback for precise positioning control. Created multi-stage filtering architecture combining input filters, common-mode chokes, and output filtering for both conducted and radiated emissions compliance. Built in safety systems with overcurrent protection, thermal monitoring, and fault detection with graceful degradation modes.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <p class="font-medium text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200 mb-1">Results:</p>
                                <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">Achieved consistent 0.1mm resolution with significantly smoother motion profile. Pre-compliance testing indicates strong likelihood of IEC 60601-1-2 certification success. Reduced design complexity and manufacturing costs. Client saves over $10K annually in direct costs plus substantial indirect savings. Delivered on-time and within budget.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Industrial Project -->
                    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-blue-100 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-blue-800/10 p-6 rounded-xl border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800/50">
                        <div class="mb-3">
                            <span class="text-xs font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wide">Industrial Control • $43K • 6 months</span>
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100 mb-3">Power Distribution Automation</h3>
                        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
                            <div>
                                <p class="font-medium text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200 mb-1">Challenge:</p>
                                <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">PDU manufacturer needed to modernize their product line to compete in marketplace. Their existing units lacked smart features that customers increasingly demanded. Legacy systems required manual monitoring with no remote visibility, alerting capabilities, or data analytics. Challenge was adding intelligence while maintaining cost competitiveness and reliability.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <p class="font-medium text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200 mb-1">Technical Approach:</p>
                                <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">Designed intelligent monitoring system using embedded Linux on ARM Cortex-A processor with large color touchscreen interface for local control and visualization. Implemented dedicated microcontroller co-processor to handle real-time external I/O interfacing, including 16-bit ADCs for high-precision current monitoring and temperature monitoring across all circuits. Added multiple communication protocols (BACnet IP, MQTT, REST APIs) with automatic failover and data buffering during network outages. Developed predictive analytics algorithms using statistical analysis and machine learning techniques to identify anomalies, thermal trends, and potential failure modes before they impact operations. Created intuitive touchscreen interface with real-time visualization, historical trending, and alarm management, plus web dashboard for remote monitoring and control from any device.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <p class="font-medium text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200 mb-1">Results:</p>
                                <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">Delivered intelligent power management system with remote monitoring, predictive maintenance, and automated alerts. Added competitive smart features that differentiate their products in marketplace. Enabled real-time visibility into power usage patterns and system health. Completed on-time and on-budget, positioning client to compete with established smart PDU manufacturers.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Scientific Project -->
                    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-purple-100 dark:from-purple-900/20 dark:to-purple-800/10 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-200 dark:border-purple-800/50">
                        <div class="mb-3">
                            <span class="text-xs font-bold text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400 uppercase tracking-wide">Scientific Instrument • $8K • 4 months</span>
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100 mb-3">Gravitometer Controller Replacement</h3>
                        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
                            <div>
                                <p class="font-medium text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200 mb-1">Challenge:</p>
                                <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">30-year-old gravitometer controller failed completely. Original manufacturer closed, zero documentation available, and replacement would cost $200K+. Legacy analog sensors worth $150K had to be preserved. Required 1µGal resolution despite multiple noise sources from aging analog components, temperature drift, and environmental vibrations.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <p class="font-medium text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200 mb-1">Technical Approach:</p>
                                <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">Complete reverse engineering of legacy analog sensor interfaces, decoding proprietary control loops and feedback mechanisms through circuit analysis and signal tracing. Designed modern 24-bit ADC front-end with precision voltage references, low-noise amplifiers, and multi-stage anti-aliasing filters to preserve signal integrity. Implemented advanced IIR filtering algorithms with adaptive coefficients to dynamically separate gravity signals from environmental noise sources including vibrations, temperature fluctuations, and electromagnetic interference. Created temperature compensation algorithms using thermal modeling and multi-point calibration data to correct for sensor drift across operating temperature range. Added modern GPS integration with NMEA protocol parsing for precise positioning coordinates and timing synchronization for data logging and remote monitoring capabilities.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <p class="font-medium text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200 mb-1">Results:</p>
                                <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">Achieved 10-15% better precision than original system with consistent 1µGal resolution. Added modern capabilities: GPS positioning, digital display, remote monitoring, and data logging. Saved client $150K+ compared to full system replacement. Equipment now provides another 15+ years of service life with improved reliability. Completed within 4-month timeline and $8K budget.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Consumer Project -->
                    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-emerald-50 to-emerald-100 dark:from-emerald-900/20 dark:to-emerald-800/10 p-5 rounded-xl border border-emerald-200 dark:border-emerald-800/50">
                        <div class="mb-3">
                            <span class="text-xs font-bold text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 uppercase tracking-wide">Consumer Electronics • $8.6K • 4 months</span>
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100 mb-3">Audio-Reactive LED System</h3>
                        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
                            <div>
                                <p class="font-medium text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200 mb-1">Challenge:</p>
                                <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">Startup needed unique audio visualization product for competitive market entry. System had to process multiple audio sources in real-time with sub-5ms latency to generate dynamic, customizable LED animations. Required BLE mobile control, 4+ hour battery life in compact form factor, and FCC Class B compliance. No existing comparable products on market.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <p class="font-medium text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200 mb-1">Technical Approach:</p>
                                <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">Designed real-time audio processing algorithms using high-performance microcontroller with DSP capabilities, implementing adaptive filtering and processing techniques to achieve sub-5ms latency with more flexibility than traditional FFT approaches. Developed custom visualization patterns with beat detection algorithms, tempo tracking, and dynamic range compression for consistent visual response across different audio sources. Implemented full BLE 5.0 stack with custom GATT services, designed for easy mobile app integration with real-time pattern customization, color scheme selection, and sensitivity adjustments. Power management uses switching regulators, dynamic voltage scaling, and intelligent sleep modes to achieve 4+ hour continuous operation from compact 12Wh lithium battery. Custom 4-layer PCB design with controlled impedance traces and EMI reduction for FCC Class B compliance. Created unique animation algorithms with multiple visualization modes responding to frequency bands, beat detection, tempo analysis, and volume dynamics with smooth transitions and customizable sensitivity parameters.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <p class="font-medium text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200 mb-1">Results:</p>
                                <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">Delivered audio visualization product with sub-5ms response time within 4-month timeline and $8.6K budget. Design built for FCC Class B compliance with EMI reduction. Achieved target battery life with room for expansion. Project completed on-time and on-budget, enabling founder to enter competitive audio visualization market. Unique feature set developed as specified positions product for direct sales success.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- How We Work -->
            <div class="bg-white dark:bg-neutral-900 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-12 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
                <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100 mb-4">Why Projects Succeed</h2>
                    <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4">
